      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/24/2/18/2",
      "text": [
        " تَلَا هَذِهِ الْآيَةَ إِنّا لَنَنْصُرُ رُسُلَنا وَ الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا فِي الْحَياةِ الدُّنْيا وَ يَوْمَ يَقُومُ الْأَشْهادُ قَالَ الْحُسَيْنُ بْنُ عَلِيٍّ مِنْهُمْ وَ لَمْ يُنْصَرْ بَعْدُ ثُمَّ قَالَ وَ اللَّهِ لَقَدْ قُتِلَ قَتَلَةُ الْحُسَيْنِ (ع) وَ لَمْ يُطْلَبْ بِدَمِهِ بَعْدُ"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayyid-mohsen-al-husayni-al-milani": [
          "2. My father narrated to me from Sa’d ibn ‘Abdillāh, from Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn ‘Isā, from Muḥammad ibn Sinān, from ‘Ali ibn Abī Ḥamzah, from Abī Basīr, who said: Abū Ja’far (Imam Bāqir (a.s.)) recited the verse, “Verily, We help Our messengers, and those who believe, in this world and on the day the witnesses shall stand forth” <a href=\"/books/quran:40#h51\">[40:51]</a>. Then Imam (a.s.) said, “Ḥusain ibn ‘Ali (a.s.) is among those described in this verse who has yet to be helped!! I swear to Allāh that the killers of Ḥusain (a.s.) were killed but his blood has not been avenged yet.”"
        ]
      }
    },
